semantic__clause.semantic__p:
Therefore, the ModSpec defines a “requirements class” as a set of requirements that must
all be passed as per the tests defined in the related conformance class (see
). Each requirements class has a one-to-one correspondence with a conformance class. A standard written to conform with the ModSpec mayuse this “module” structure in any manner consistent with the rest of the ModSpec.

